commit.message:
Remove "z." → "ず" entry from AZIK rom-kana rules

This rule is not mentioned on the official AZIK page, and unlike the similar
"zc", "zv", "zf", and "zx" rules, the original keystroke (zu) is not difficult
to type. And it masks the DDSKK-derived "z." → "…" shortcut.
